{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"895c1193-95c6-4829-bd78-e9f1f6d8fb70","content":"Here's what you need to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or**, if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp` instead:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- For xUnit v2 (your current version): -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n\n   <!-- OR upgrade to xUnit v3: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n   This lets `dotnet test` use MTP instead of VSTest.\n\n4. **Set output type** to `Exe` (MTP requires a runnable test host):\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n5. **Run tests** as usual:\n\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n\n> **Tip:** If you're open to upgrading to xUnit v3, that's the recommended path — it has native MTP support and is actively developed. xUnit v2's MTP runner (`xunit.runner.mtp`) is a compatibility bridge.\n\nWould you like help applying these changes to a specific project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"10849345-99b3-491e-83d2-78d96ac50fed","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using `xunit.runner.visualstudio`) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":471,"requestId":"CFEC:2441A9:5F9CB29:6ACCEE8:69EC0DF6"},"id":"95a1ddec-9321-4805-b905-188e271a4306","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:42:41.228Z","parentId":"37dbab60-9ae1-454c-a6c4-882d88d3db9f"}
